          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For example, if searching for Feb 29 in the Gregorian calendar, the algorithm may choose March 1 instead (for example, if the year is not a leap year). If you wish to find the next Feb 29 without the algorithm adjusting the next higher component in the specified ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "DateComponents",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", then use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "strict",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " option.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "There are ultimately implementation-defined limits in how far distant the search will go.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
